main event: On August 9, 1955, in San Diego, California, a disc-shaped silver object was observed flying from west to east for 35 seconds.
interesting points: The observation was classified as a Ground-Visual type.
There was one object observed, described as disc-shaped and silver in color.
The possibility of it being a jet aircraft was considered, but no conclusive explanation was determined.
The report indicates that there was a photo taken during the observation.
The object flew level during the entire 35-second observation period.
